DESCRIPTION: Unique identifier assigned to each application submitted for processing to the Chicago National Processing Center.
Status associated with the last significant event or decision. Valid values include “Certified,” “Certified-Withdrawn,” Denied,” and “Withdrawn”.
Date and time the application was submitted.
Date on which the last significant event or decision was recorded by the Chicago National Processing Center.
Indicates the type of temporary application submitted for processing. R = H-1B; A = E-3 Australian; C = H-1B1 Chile; S = H-1B1 Singapore.  Also referred to as “Program” in prior years.
Name of employer submitting labor condition application.
Trade Name or dba name of employer submitting labor condition application, if applicable.
Contact information of the Employer requesting temporary labor certification.
Y = Employer is represented by an Agent or Attorney; N = Employer is not represented by an Agent or Attorney.
Name of Agent or Attorney filing an H-1B application on behalf of the employer.
